"It's odd. Looking back at my instincts, which I often felt were boorish and beneath me, I see now that my need for proof is so natural, so human. Good, even. When I create smoke tests that produce visual results and detailed, useful explanations, I feel like they set my projects up for success.
When I first started coding, I remember how often I felt discouraged by the enormous complexity of things like Transformers and Pillow. But then I discovered Python packages and projects that let me upload something simple, make a few changes here and there, and just like that, they destroyed all fear.
They cultivated hope.
More than programming, I think I'm in the business of cultivating hope. For anyone and everyone who dreams that they, too, may change the world."




